          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688729690098-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meatballs have lightly browned, transfer them to a plate and set aside (these will finish cooking in the sauce later)</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat and once hot, add the <strong>remaining diced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomato has slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>remaining chicken stock mix</strong> and 190ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[320ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688729695736-x200.jpg",
