            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rub the <strong>reserved garlic</strong> over the cut side of the <strong>toasted ciabatta base</strong>, then layer on the <strong>reserved spinach</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomatoey pork meatballs</strong> and any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>tomato sauce</strong> from the pan to the <strong>ciabatta base</strong> and top with the<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and the <strong>toasted ciabatta lid</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the garlic and fresh spinach leaves!</span></strong></p><p>Season to taste and enjoy!</p>",
